Description: Small startup with patent pending on new security system design.
Full Description: Small startup with patent pending on new security system design.   Many advancements have been made with Enhanced 911 systems - these systems do improve outside response times, however, once outside agencies arrive on the scene, they still need to gain access to a facility.  Our system relies on trained on site first responders who can effectively neutralize an active shooter.  These first responders are already being placed in schools across the country - they can be professional security guards, law enforcement officers or in some cases, teachers and other school staff.   They need immediate and accurate position information to get them to the scene of an emergency - The Dragon Net provides this service.   The Dragon Net will augment existing security systems in an affordable platform - or can stand alone in remote facilities or outdoor venues where large groups of people gather for work, entertainment or education.   It's designed to empower the staff at these various facilities with the knowledge that if something terrible happens, someone will be there in seconds.    Many facilities continue to add layers of access control and physical barrier systems to restrict entrance.  These systems can be breached and we have seen that those barrier systems can also restrict outside agencies when they are needed on site during an emergency.  Our system is designed to provide security from the inside out.  911 is also notified, so they will be on the way.  There are precious few moments to act and  we must act from within.
Industry Groups: Education, Information Technology, Internet Services, Messaging and Telecommunications, Privacy and Security

Description: The QCA First Funds are a family of small investment funds which were established in 2003 to help fledgling companies reach important
Full Description: The QCA First Funds are a family of small investment funds which were established in 2003 to help fledgling companies reach important milestones in their development and attract additional investment from conventional sources.  They have been created by matching investments from the State of Ohio's Third Frontier Action Fund.  Members of the Queen City Angels, with support from the Tri-State Growth Capital Fund and others, provide management and oversight of the Fund, as well as mentoring and guidance to the portfolio companies. In 2006, a second Fund was established to continue the work.  QCA First Fund II received support from the same sources as the original Fund, and has completed its investment activities. In 2009, QCA First Fund III was created.  This Fund is somewhat larger, and has received matching investment from the Ohio Capital Fund in addition to the others mentioned above. In late 2013, we began making investments from our our largest fund to date.  QCA First Fund IV will continue the work of the previous Funds to help start-up companies meet their initial growth objectives and attract additional investment.

Description: On Monday, Kin Clinton, CEO of Woolsthorpe Technologies, told VNC he has learned the hard way that Nashville's healthcare prowess isn't
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: On Monday, Kin Clinton, CEO of Woolsthorpe Technologies, told VNC he has learned the hard way that Nashville's healthcare prowess isn't nearly as well recognized among U.S. money-center investors as he wanted to believe. For months, Brentwood-based Clinton has been scouting for sorely needed venture capital to bring his cardiovascular monitor to market.  If Nashville money doesn't soon step up, Clinton may be forced to deal with investors who'd require he relocate the company. He said Wednesday that of four potential investors (none from Nashville) who are currently in pre-deal due diligence with him, "ALL firms have heartburn about this being a Nashville-based company." During Clinton's sorties to such investment watering-holes as Menlo Park-Palo Alto and New York City, he said he was "disappointed" to find that in the minds of investors there, "Nashville doesn't even exist." Wednesday, a similar conclusion was delivered by a panel of experts assembled for "Financing the Deal," a conference sponsored by the Nashville Health Care Council and attended by more than 450 executives. Not to worry: Program moderator Senator Bill Frist, M.D., now a partner with Cressey & Company, said that no matter how flat the rest of the economy gets, how steeply banks "deleverage" or who's in the White House come January, "we're going to be putting more money in healthcare."  Still, if Nashville casts a smaller-than-expected shadow on the investment landscape, that could limit local companies' and investors' participation in the next wave of growth.

It wasn't long before Michael started installing golf greens for his neighbors and received countless referrals from that point forward. Since then, the former CPA from Westchester grew to become the expert in golf green putting installations throughout the tri-state area - and he's even traveled as far as Hawaii to install a putting green for the Bank of Hawaii. HGA's list of clients is constantly growing and among them are some of the most notable in the business, including CEO's, celebrities and fortune 100 companies and many more. Michael's obsession with detail, design and perfection shines through his work with each golf green installation. Description: A tech company for the entertainment & media industry, owned-and-operated by two women, web pioneering, software engineers.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Westside Websites is a tech company in Los Angeles owned-and-operated by two women, web pioneering, software engineers — Camille Alcasid and Sandra Jimenez. Together, the duo brings an exceptional level of expertise to all stages of a web application's lifecycle, customized to each project's resources, methodology, budget and timeline. (As their personal giveback to the industry, they also launched Wonder Women Coders (an in-person course that teaches women to code and engineer for the web) and Women's Production Society (a social organization comprised of 80+ women in Physical Production Executive positions, primarily VP and above, working in Film, Television, Streaming and other Media). Camille started her career in 1995, as one of the first web developers for Comcast-NBCUniversal, producing nbc4la.com (the very first local TV news website in Los Angeles). A couple of years later, Sandra joined Camille as the Senior Developer for a tech-startup now known as zap2it.com, a popular TV listings & news website. Camille and Sandra worked together, once again, as Executive and Senior Consultants to spearhead the launch of e-business for top music companies like EMI, Sony, Universal, and WEA. Camille then set her sights on creating a content management system for the TV industry, in which BAMTOOLS was born. Meanwhile, Sandra was recruited by carsdirect.com as a Senior Java Developer, where she mastered Enterprise Commerce. Eventually, Camille and Sandra rejoined forces to create Westside Websites, an innovative web engineering company dedicated to providing digital solutions for Entertainment & News, Corporate Intranet and Extranet, Crowd-Funding, Contest, Promotion, Video Streaming, Email Blast, Group Message Boards, Content Management Systems, and Text-to-Vote, to name a few. Most recently in 2019, Camille and Sandra has entered the AI space after winning in an AT&T hackathon with their Wonder Women Coders. The women banded together to innovate and bring their application to market — an exciting new way for to utilize visual, gesture, audio, and speech-to-text recognition using element detection within videos. "We're invaluable to sales and marketing teams, not just IT," says Sandra, "We solve roadblocks and improve efficiency in ways companies communicate with each other and/or their target audience through digital solutions." "Our clients hire us to execute their creative concepts using the latest web technology," adds Camille, "We also enjoy collaborating with many advertising and creative agencies in town as their tech counterpart." With over 25+ years of development experience under their belt, Westside Websites boasts an impressive client list, featuring prestigious corporations which include Twentieth Television, Western Digital, MyNetworkTV, NBCUniversal, Tribune, FXX, Kingworld, Sony, and Telemundo. Looking towards the future, Westside Websites continues to make strides in being a reputable force in the digital world.
Industry Groups: Apps, Commerce and Shopping, Design, Internet Services, Software

Full Description: ARESCOM INC. is a global provider of broadband and wireless (802.11) infrastructure equipment and services for the rapidly expanding broadband marketplace. ARESCOM is dedicated to delivering the most user-friendly, cost-effective, and customer-tailored high-speed broadband access solutions to meet the growing business needs of the hospitality, residential property, telecommunication and SME (Small & Medium Enterprises) marketplace worldwide. Founded in the Silicon Valley, in 1996, ARESCOM designs, manufactures and markets a comprehensive line of broadband and wireless (802.11) Internet access solutions, ranging from The ARESCOM Hospitality Network (AHN) service for the booming worldwide hospitality market to the most simple DSL bridge/modem CPE (Customer Premise Equipment) for the home and small business user. All ARESCOM DSL broadband access equipment includes easy-to-use GUI-based remote management and sophisticated routing technology software packages for simplified setup, extensive network management and global network connectivity capabilities. Currently, ARESCOM’s DSL broadband access equipment is widely deployed by major telecommunication carriers, ISPs, and System Integrators worldwide. ARESCOM’s DSL broadband access solutions include the ARESCOM MTU (Multi-Tenant Unit) CDS 6000 DSL Service Platform, a fully featured DSL broadband service platform, provides a complete family of easily-scalable multi-access and multi-service controllers, concentrator modules, as well as global billing server systems to target the growing MTU hospitality, commercial and residential marketplace. The CDS 6000 functions as a sophisticated DSLAR (DSLAM + Router) located at the MTU site, connecting to tenants or guestroom CPE equipment via the telephone wiring, supporting advanced routing features, subscriber management functions, usage billing functions, and a wide range of WAN interface options, including OC-3/STM1, T1/E1, 10/100 Base T, and V.35. ARESCOM has already established itself as one of the world’s leading DSL CPE providers with its NetDSL modem and router family. The AHN (ARESCOM Hospitality Network) service solution has the most advanced Hospitality and Residential property broadband and wireless features in the market today targeted to address the emerging need of offering broadband Internet access in public areas.

Description: Enveloc Inc. is an offsite data backup and storage provider with corporate headquarters in the USA
Full Description: Founded in 1995, Enveloc, Inc. is a privately held, full service offsite data backup and storage provider with corporate headquarters in the USA Technology and Research Park in Mobile, Alabama. The company owns server clusters located in secure Network Operation Centers in Mobile and Los Angeles. At Enveloc, they offer the industry's safest, most efficient means of data protection and recovery. Capable of running on any Windows operating system, Enveloc securely and automatically transmits data to geographically-diverse Class A Network Operation Centers located over 2,000 miles apart, providing safe, complete, and redundant copies of your data. Enveloc Remote Backup features daily backup verification and audits, as well as immediate, around the clock professional assistance from technical experts who appreciate the significance of your data.  Enveloc provides live technical support 24/7, at no charge during business hours as well as after-hours emergency restoration assistance. For clients lacking an IT staff, remote support via their software or website is also available for system configuration and assistance, if needed.

Description: Ologeez is a peer-review literature search, recommendation engine, and group collaboration for academics and industry professionals.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Peer-review literature search, recommendation engine and group collaboration for academics and industry professionals. Developed by a Stanford graduate student to help find more relevant papers for his Ph.D. research in genetics. Tied into the science literature database, PubMed, and through user contributed peer-reviewed papers, it makes finding and discussing papers a lot easier. Other academic and industry databases to follow. After developing the literature part, it was a natural progression to make a network for those using the site. Groups can be created to share publications, protocols, AJAX calendars, and create forum discussions. Local and University seminars and conferences can be uploaded and searched based on your academic interests. The site is free to use and free from advertising.
